---
import FlowbarLayout from "../../layouts/FlowbarLayout.astro";
---

<FlowbarLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Flowbar"
  description="FlowBar stores all your data locally on your device. We do not collect, transmit, or have access to any of your personal information."
>
  <div class="policy-area">
    <div class="policy-card">
      <div class="policy-content">
        <h1>Privacy Policy for FlowBar</h1>
        <p class="updated">Last updated: April 8, 2026</p>

        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          FlowBar ("the app", "we", "our") is a macOS menu bar productivity app.
          This policy explains what data the app collects, how it is stored, and
          how it is used.
        </p>
        <p class="highlight">
          Short version: FlowBar stores all your data locally on your device. We
          do not collect, transmit, or have access to any of your personal
          information.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          FlowBar does not collect any personal data. The app operates entirely
          on your device.
        </p>
        <p>
          The following information is stored <strong
            >locally on your Mac only</strong
          >:
        </p>

        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Data</th>
              <th>Where stored</th>
              <th>Purpose</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Task titles and notes</td>
              <td>Application Support (JSON files)</td>
              <td>Core app functionality</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Task completion history</td>
              <td>Application Support (JSON files)</td>
              <td>History and Focus Stats</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Pomodoro session count</td>
              <td>UserDefaults</td>
              <td>Daily progress tracking</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>App preferences (theme, timer duration, etc.)</td>
              <td>UserDefaults</td>
              <td>Personalization</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Pro purchase status</td>
              <td>StoreKit / UserDefaults</td>
              <td>Unlocking Pro features</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Panel window position</td>
              <td>UserDefaults</td>
              <td>Remembering your layout</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>None of this data ever leaves your device.</p>

        <hr />

        <h2>In-App Purchases</h2>
        <p>
          FlowBar offers a one-time <strong>FlowBar Pro</strong> purchase processed
          entirely through <strong>Apple's App Store / StoreKit</strong>. We do
          not see, store, or process any payment information. Apple handles all
          billing. Please refer to <a
            href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/"
            target="_blank">Apple's Privacy Policy</a
          > for how Apple processes purchase data.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Notifications</h2>
        <p>
          FlowBar may send <strong>local notifications</strong> (e.g., Pomodoro timer
          complete). These are generated on your device and are never transmitted
          to any server. You can disable notifications at any time in <strong
            >System Settings → Notifications → FlowBar</strong
          >.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>macOS Shortcuts Integration</h2>
        <p>
          FlowBar optionally integrates with the macOS Shortcuts app to enable
          Focus Mode (Do Not Disturb) toggling. This uses a local URL scheme (<code
            >shortcuts://</code
          >) and runs entirely on your device. No data is sent to external
          servers.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>No Third-Party Analytics or Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          FlowBar does not use any third-party analytics, advertising SDKs,
          crash-reporting services, or tracking frameworks. We have no
          visibility into how you use the app.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>No Account Required</h2>
        <p>
          FlowBar does not require you to create an account. No email address,
          name, or any other identifying information is ever requested or
          collected.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not share, sell, rent, or trade any data — because we do not
          collect any.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          All app data is stored in your Mac's Application Support folder and
          UserDefaults. To delete all data:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Quit FlowBar.</li>
          <li>Delete the app from your Applications folder.</li>
          <li>
            Remove the app data folder: <code
              >~/Library/Application Support/FlowBar/</code
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            Remove preferences: open Terminal and run <code
              >defaults delete com.kmino.FlowBar</code
            >
          </li>
        </ol>

        <hr />

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          FlowBar does not knowingly collect data from anyone, including
          children under the age of 13.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          If we ever change this policy in a material way (e.g., if a future
          version adds network features), we will update the "Last updated" date
          above and note the changes in the App Store release notes.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p><a href="mailto:contact@kmino.io">contact@kmino.io</a></p>

        <hr />

        <p class="footer-note">FlowBar is developed by Kmino.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</FlowbarLayout>

<style>
  .policy-area {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    width: 560px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .policy-area {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 560px;
    }
  }

  .policy-card {
    background: rgba(245, 245, 245, 0.9);
    backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
    border-radius: 20px;
    box-shadow:
      0px 17px 45px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5),
      0px 0px 1px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
    width: 100%;
    max-height: calc(100vh - 300px);
    overflow-y: auto;
    pointer-events: auto;
    scrollbar-width: thin;
    scrollbar-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2) transparent;
  }

  .policy-content {
    padding: clamp(24px, 3vw, 40px);
  }

  .policy-content h1 {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 20px;
    letter-spacing: 0.31em;
    text-align: center;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .updated {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #888;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .policy-content h2 {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin: 20px 0 8px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .policy-content p,
  .policy-content li {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #3a3a3a;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .policy-content ol {
    padding-left: 20px;
  }

  .policy-content a {
    color: #a89a3a;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .policy-content code {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.07);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-family: monospace;
  }

  .policy-content hr {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    margin: 20px 0;
  }

  .highlight {
    background: rgba(204, 187, 101, 0.15);
    border-left: 3px solid #ccbb65;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  th {
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
    color: #1a1a1a;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  td {
    padding: 6px 8px;
    color: #3a3a3a;
    font-weight: 300;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .footer-note {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #aaa;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
